    "In addition to node clustering and node sampling, there exist some other ways of hierarchical pooling methods, such as tree-based hierarchical graph pooling methods, which implement the coarsening graph process by encoding trees.",
    "These methods aim to preserve the key structural and feature information in the graph in different ways.",
    "Node clustering pooling is to merge nodes to get new nodes by forming clusters by nodes, in other words, the key point of the node clustering pooling method is to learn the soft assignment matrix of the nodes making the nodes be reasonably allocated to the clusters, the pooling process of node clustering can be denoted as:",
    "where S l ∈ R n l ×n l+1 denotes the learnable node cluster assignment matrix, and n l denotes the number of clusters at layer l.",
